{
  "texts": [
    "Recent studies on the use of generative AI in marketing research suggest promising possibilities for large language models (LLMs) to serve as substitutes for human participants in market research.",
    "(Goli and Singh 2024; Li et al. 2024).",
    "Third, the content generation process of our studies depends on the specific prompts we designed and the generative AI models used.",
    "Alternative prompts could yield substantially different outputs, potentially altering the results of our investigations.",
    "Future research may benefit from a more granular approach to control the outputs of generative AI systems, such as ChatGPT."
  ]
}